					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">All meemory accesses require M2 to be high (that's the way the CPU indicates a read/write request).  For WRAM at $6000-7FFF, you want to activate the chip when A13, A14, PRG /CE, and M2 are all high.  The NES memory map does not define anything from $4018-7FFF, so anything can be mapped there.  Though $8000-FFFF was intended for PRG-ROM, mapper hardware can override this mapping setup by doing its own address decoding.  You can reassign $8000-FFFF to something other than ROM, or you can add ROM to the $4018-7FFF range if desired.</div>

					
